title: Nonaqueous electrolyte solution and nonaqueous electrolyte secondary battery

events.title: Application filed by Mitsubishi Chemical Corp

classifications.description: Liquid materials characterised by the additives
Rocking-chair batteries, i.e. batteries with lithium insertion or intercalation in both electrodes; Lithium-ion batteries
Accumulators with non-aqueous electrolyte characterised by the materials used as electrolytes, e.g. mixed inorganic/organic electrolytes
Liquid materials characterised by the solvents
Safety or regulating additives or arrangements in electrodes, separators or electrolyte
Electrodes based on metals, Si or alloys
Silicon or alloys based on silicon
Carbonaceous material, e.g. graphite-intercalation compounds or CFx

abstract: The invention provides a nonaqueous electrolyte solution and a nonaqueous electrolyte secondary battery, wherein the nonaqueous electrolyte solution contains an electrolyte, a nonaqueous solvent and a compound represented by the following general formula (1), and the nonaqueous electrolyte secondary battery can inhibit the decomposition of the electrolyte solution and inhibit the aging of the battery when the battery is used in a high-temperature environment, and has high capacity, excellent storage characteristics and cycle characteristics and high energy density. In the general formula (1), R1、R2And R3Each independently represents a hydrogen atom, a cyano group, or a hydrocarbon group having 1 to 10 carbon atoms with or without a halogen atom. R1And R2Not simultaneously hydrogen atoms.
claims:
1、一种非水系电解液，其用于具备正极和负极的非水系电解液二次电池，所述正极具有能够包藏和释放金属离子的正极活性物质，所述负极具有能够包藏和释放金属离子的含有选自由Si、Sn和Pb组成的组中的至少一种原子的负极活性物质，所述非水系电解液的特征在于，其含有以下述通式(1)表示的化合物和/或结构式中具有2个以上且4个以下氰基的化合物，1. A non-aqueous electrolyte, which is used in a non-aqueous electrolyte secondary battery with a positive pole and a negative pole, the positive pole has a positive active material capable of enclosing and releasing metal ions, and the negative pole has a material capable of enclosing and releasing metal ions. A negative electrode active material containing at least one atom selected from the group consisting of Si, Sn and Pb, the non-aqueous electrolyte is characterized in that it contains a compound represented by the following general formula (1) and/or in the structural formula Compounds having 2 or more and 4 or less cyano groups,
      
      
        
          
            
          
          
        
      
      
         通式(1)中，R1、R2和R3各自独立地表示氢原子、氰基或者具有或不具有卤原子的碳原子数为1～10的烃基。In the general formula (1), R 1 , R 2 and R 3 each independently represent a hydrogen atom, a cyano group, or a hydrocarbon group having 1 to 10 carbon atoms which may or may not have a halogen atom.

2、一种非水系电解液，其特征在于，通式(1)中，R1和R2中的一个或者两个各自独立地是氰基或者具有或不具有卤原子的碳原子数为1～10的烃基。2. A non-aqueous electrolytic solution, characterized in that, in the general formula ( 1 ), one or two of R and R are independently cyano or have or have no halogen atom and the number of carbon atoms is 1 ~10 hydrocarbon groups.

The non-aqueous electrolytic solution according to claim 1, wherein the compound represented by general formula (1) is selected from the group consisting of acrylonitrile, methacrylonitrile, butenenitrile, 3-methylbutenenitrile, 2-Methyl-2-butenenitrile, 2-pentenenitrile, 2-methyl-2-pentenenitrile, 1-cyano-1-cyclopentene, 1-cyano-1-cyclohexene, At least one compound selected from the group consisting of geranonitrile, cinnamonitrile, 2-furoylnitrile, fumaronitrile and tetracyanoethylene.
